      {
        "id": 2348478,
        "name": "Jayson Cohen",
        "username": "Jayson_Cohen",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/8797f3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-01-29T13:55:14.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks for the note. Great to see a Savigny of this age not only drinking well but seemingly on a stable trajectory for the future.</p>\n<p>Was this a bottle picked up recently or was this from the cellar?</p>\n<p>The Boillot family history is somewhat fascinating and a bit confusing, even putting aside how many branches there are.  Do you know if Jean was in charge of the domaine when this wine was made or was his father Henri still in control?  I\u2019m also curious if this is the identical parcel worked today or if it has been expanded or any of it sold off as current Henri has expanded the (direct line) domaine into other vineyard holdings.</p>",
        "post_number": 6,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 10,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T02:53:35.319Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
        "reply_to_post_number": null,
