      {
        "id": 2348795,
        "name": "Arnt Egil Nordlien",
        "username": "Arnt_Egil_Nordlien",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/9e8a1a/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-01-29T20:34:49.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The '79s was made by Henris brother Jean-Marc. His last vintage was '83. But it was the brothers father Jean that was in charge of the operation. Father Jean and son Jean-Marc disagreed on the future of the domaine and Jean-Marc left and made the first vintages of Olivier Leflaive (1984-1988). Jean-Marcs grandfather was so impressed with the work his grandson did at Leflaive that he let Jean-Marc inherit half of his vineyards (so I guess he still had the ownership). So Jean-Marc startet his own domaine with these in 1989.</p>",
