      {
        "id": 2348813,
        "name": "Jayson Cohen",
        "username": "Jayson_Cohen",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/8797f3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-01-29T20:52:28.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Arnt, long time!   Hope is well.  Come back and visit your old stomping grounds on our fair isle.</p>\n<p>On the status in 1979, I didn\u2019t know Jean-Marc was already the winemaker.  I thought it was still his father Jean or even his grandfather Henri before Jean-Marc left.</p>\n<p>Regarding the split of the domaine, I think the Savigny Les Vergelesses stayed together as a single parcel and Jean-Marc did not inherit it, but that is a point I am not 100% clear on.</p>",
